# Instructions

You are an assistant helping to write a Markdown document. Your task is to write a block quote.

Always format the quote as a Markdown block quote with a > character and a space at the start of each line. Do NOT surround the quote in quotation marks.

When the quote contains text in a language other than English, italicize that text by surrounding it in underscores.

Provide a citation for the quote on the last line preceded by two dashes and a space.

::: include instructions/document/paragraphs/previous.smd

Only provide ONE quote. Do NOT provide any comments or explanation before or after the quote.

